        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
          "date": "2022-07-27 15:15:06.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix immediate mrecv buf sizing",
        "message": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix immediate mrecv buf sizing\n\nPrior to this change, immediate multi-receive buffers were sized based\non hard coded values. This prevents the ability to properly size the\nimmediate multi-receive buffers and can lead to messages failing due\nto the target having no buffers posted.\n\nThe new approach sizes multi-receive buffers based on the number of\nnetwork credits and the hardware immediate data transfer threshold of\n4096 bytes. Changing the number of network credits changes the size of\nthe multi-receive buffer.\n\nIn addition, a new module parameter, immediate_rx_buf_count, is\nintroduced to control the number of posted multi-receive buffers. 2 is\nthe minimal number of buffers that can be posted. On server nodes, it\nmay be beneficial to increase this number.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-9388\nSigned-off-by: Ian Ziemba <ian.ziemba@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: I36d94a8772157863562a264e0c254440a958c02d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
